ibrary at Nanterre</p></scopecontent></c01><c01 id="aspace_44563b58ed65ce215ae215d3865c4554" level="file"><did><unittitle>PRO - PREM 314 + FO</unittitle><unitdate calendar="gregorian" era="ce" normal="1945/1945">1945</unitdate><container id="aspace_4ce2bf342dd478c9e319c71f767c3f04" label="Mixed Materials [31924065182382]" type="box">1</container><container id="aspace_5d2086d0e1e8aa9fa5a97e8011d06436" parent="aspace_4ce2bf342dd478c9e319c71f767c3f04" type="folder">5-6</container></did><scopecontent id="aspace_669fb89da0b2e7f65b08d266a15294ea"><head>Scope and Contents</head><p>Classified documents on French Indo-China from Public Records Office (Foreign Office documents)</p></scopecontent></c01><c01 id="aspace_40e26f05a69d014871b2b4106e486296" level="file"><did><unittitle>Mary Speers' Notes</unittitle><unitdate calendar="gregorian" era="ce" normal="1942/1943" type="inclusive">1942-1943</unitdate><container id="aspace_cf501857e8e5d2071942c0dfa2734cd7" label="Mixed Materials [31924065182382]" type="box">1</container><container id="aspace_68bbff25863dfe058ba9c9f3e16d6ccf" parent="aspace_cf501857e8e5d2071942c0dfa2734cd7" type="folder">7</container></did><scopecontent id="aspace_2fb37c646720f4ad11ac37885ab965b4"><head>Scope and Contents</head><p>Foreign Office series 371/35921, ff. Mostly on wartime relations with France.</p></scopecontent></c01><c01 id="aspace_66374441566d62f006507bd57881470f" level="file"><did><unittitle>My Notes 1980 - PRO &amp; Rhodes House</unittitle><unitdate calendar="gregorian" era="ce" normal="1980/1980">1980</unitdate><container id="aspace_16178f047c75b37687db62015363bec4" label="Mixed Materials [31924065182382]" type="box">1</container><container id="aspace_8534f3c075127076b461ee5f124cb241" parent="aspace_16178f047c75b37687db62015363bec4" type="folder">8</container></did><scopecontent id="aspace_15da68ac1d332fa320352b6d9de99815"><head>Scope and Contents</head><p>CAB 121/741 - Notes taken on memos on Indochina for PM from Foreign Section. File: "M